description: Returns an array of resources in the organization's accounts that are available to be associated with a resource set.

parameters.name: MemberAccountIds
parameters.description: The Amazon Web Services account IDs to discover resources in. Only one account is supported per request. The account must be a member of your organization. (string) ---

parameters.name: ResourceType
parameters.description: The type of resources to discover.

nested_items.name: Items
nested_items.description: Details of the resources that were discovered.

nested_items.name: URI
nested_items.description: The universal resource identifier (URI) of the discovered resource.

nested_items.name: AccountId
nested_items.description: The Amazon Web Services account ID associated with the discovered resource.

nested_items.name: Type
nested_items.description: The type of the discovered resource.

nested_items.name: Name
nested_items.description: The name of the discovered resource.

nested_items.name: NextToken
nested_items.description: When you request a list of objects with a MaxResults setting, if the number of objects that are still available for retrieval exceeds the maximum you requested, Firewall Manager returns a NextToken value in the response. To retrieve the next batch of objects, use the token returned from the prior request in your next request.
